	(115, 'The Florios of Sicily: A Novel', 'Stefania Auci (author), Katherine Gregor (translator)', 'Based on the true history of the uncrowned kings of Sicily: the story of a family, restless and ambitious, shrewd and determined to be richer and more powerful than anybody else. ', '2024-07-08'),
	(88, 'The Pillars of the Earth - The Kingsbridge Novels', 'Ken Follett', 'Hugely redolent of the medieval clash of politics, avarice and religion, The Pillars of the Earth is, first and foremost, a ripping good yarn which grafts timeless themes of ambition, lust and jealousy onto a compelling tale of cathedral building. Follett is a top notch storyteller and this wildly enjoyable volume spawned two sequels to form The Kingsbridge Series.', '2017-07-13'),
